{
  "texts": [
    "Lungs or ChestThe most frequently discussed topic in pulmonary image processing from ct imaging and radiography is the identification, description, and categorization of tumors.Numerous studies evaluate CNNs with traditional machine learning techniques employing handmade features or supplement current feature sets with deep network-derived features.",
    "With an unified technique, numerous organizations may identify various illnesses with a lung X-ray.",
    "Another well-liked study area in CT is the identification of topographical features suggestive of interstitial pulmonary disorders [186][187][188].The most frequent radiological examination is a chest X-ray, and various studies have used a huge collection of images and textual descriptions to build algorithms that integrate CNNs for visual interpretation and RNNs for textual processing.",
    "In the foreseeable future, we anticipate seeing additional study in this area [189][190][191].All of the highest approaches in a current competition for tumor identification in CT, LUNA16, utilized CNN frameworks.",
    "In comparison, ANODE09's chest tumor identification challenge included handmade characteristics to categorize potential nodules."
  ]
}